Tech Stack

Python 3.11+
SQLite — lightweight, no server, fast enough for ~2M rows
openpyxl — read xlsx
Streamlit — rapid UI, built-in filters/tables/charts
pandas — data manipulation during ingest

MVP Scope (Phase 1)

Ingest pipeline: xlsx → SQLite
All filters working
Company results table with all columns
Drill-down to individual LCAs
Basic sorting

Phase 2 (Post-MVP)

USCIS employer data join → approval rate column
PERM data join → green card sponsorship signal
Export filtered results to CSV
Charts: top sponsors by role, wage distributions, geographic heatmap
Saved filter presets
SOC code autocomplete/lookup

Setup Instructions (for README.md)

cd ~/Desktop && mkdir h1b-explorer && cd h1b-explorer
Download LCA xlsx files from DOL site into data/
pip install -r requirements.txt
python src/ingest.py — builds h1b.db
streamlit run src/app.py
